"Art falls into two categories--\. No, not the art. My bad. Artists
"There are the ones who see something taking place in the world.
Maybe it's wrongdoings of their fellow pedestrians, maybe it's
abuse of power by those sitting on top of the pyramid scheme..."
"Whatever it is, it feeds their inspiration and creativity and
they desperately want put their own spin on it."
"It might be in hopes of retaining something very brief in history
or it might be out of agony they feel for the world."
"It must be very sponteneous I imagine. Painting a picture in an
inspired frenzy or composing a piece of music that beats in sync
"Then there are the other half of poor sods. The ones who dwell in
"They want to paint a picture of their inner world. Maybe in hopes
that someone else would understand them a little bit better..."
"...Or maybe they want to reach the few people who share the
"Naturally this doesn't exclude the possibility that these people
wouldn't want to depict a picture of times as well. But they would
do that only if they saw parallels to their own small circles."
"If the event taking place would strike a chord with the monologue
they are having with the world."
"Both sound selfish in their own right. There are the extroverted
artists who benefit from the sufferings of the others."
"While introverted artists on the other hand sound very self-centered,
only wanting to talk about themselves."
"Now that I think about it... There might be a third kind as well."
"Authors who don't even have a clear picture in mind when they
"They let the story write itself, let the brush strokes dictate
the direction of the story instead trying to force their own will
"Such chaotic process can lead to unexplored directions."
"Inspiration can be a chaotic process, don't you think?"
"Say old sport... The one who dreams all this... The dreamer buried
"Which type do you think she is?"
"'She'? I thought you were talking about someone else?"
"I'm not one to argue. Or give answers for that matter. But I do
think you got a point there."
"Right? It does sometimes feel like that."
"I do wonder though. Things are rarely so straightforward."
"Ah, I let my bias shine through and you followed on it."
"Still, I think you might be right there my friend."
"'She'? I thought you were talking about someone else?"
"The big yellow face looming in the sky? Or someone else entirely?"
"I fear our signals are getting tangled here. Maybe we do not
share the kind of connection I first imagined..."
"It is a sad day. To realize you've grown apart from days gone."

"The exhibition on show here in Bohemia National Museum dives
deep into the various religious beliefs around the world."
"Alll-mer - The Ascended One is a great example on how different
these perspectives can really be when examining them through the
"In Europa Alll-mer is often depicted as a male with caucasian facial
features, a bald head and a muscular body."
"In the Eastern Sanctuaries Alll-mer is often described according
to his earlier depictions when he was still just a mortal."
"In these images he is often thinner than his western counterpart
and sports a longer hair, closer to how he was described before
ascending and losing all his bodily hair."
"Naturally his facial features often depict him as a native to
"The western depictions highlight his godly stature, whereas in
the Eastern Sanctuaries he is more humanized."
